name: Beigel Bake
headline: Enjoy a traditional salt beef bagel at Beigel Bake
address_text: Beigel Bake, 159 Brick Ln, Shoreditch, London E1 6SB
description_html: Beigel Bake is a cornerstone of the Brick Lane neighbourhood, selling takeaway bagels 24 hours a day and known for having a queue down the block. They are famous for their bagels, baked in the traditional Jewish style, served with hot salf beef and mustard Their other options include sweet pastries and alternative savory bagels (but we're telling you, get the salt beef). Not a surprise that Beigel Bake produces 7,000 beigels every day.

name: The Escapologist
headline: Get delicious creative cocktails and all-star happy hour deals at the Escapologist
address_text: The Escapologist, 35 Earlham Street, Covent Garden, London WC2H 9LD
description_html: The Escapologist is a quirky underground bar with "unique" art and a buzzing atmosphere. Their happy hour is not to be missed, where you can score 2 for 1 cocktails, that promise to be embellished with some form of candy, colors or other unique twist. High recommendation for their Espresso Martini.

name: Gordon's Wine Bar
headline: Grab a bottle of wine in the candlelight, in the vaulted cellars of Gordon's Wine Bar
address_text: Gordon's Wine Bar, 47 Villiers St, Charing Cross, London WC2N 6NE,
description_html: Gordon's Wine Bar is perfect for a cosy and romantic glass of wine - it was built in a 19th century vaulted cellar and is lit with candles. Is is also quite popular, so at prime times you may need to be crafty to grab a table in the underground rooms - not suprising for London's oldest wine bar. The wine list is international and top notch and has options to suit all price ranges.

name: Iris Bar at the Gherkin
headline: Enjoy the best 360 London views in London and have a cocktail at Iris bar in the Gherkin
address_text: Iris Bar at the Gherkin, 30 St Mary Axe, London EC3A 8EP
description_html: Impress your date with what are arguably the best skyline views in London at this gorgeous 360 rooftop bar. The rooftop is covered so you'll be safe from the elements (no promises about the safety of your wallet). This one must be booked ahead and is the perfect spot for an romantic date or a special occasion. Don't forget to bring ID to get past build security.

name: The Alchemist
headline: Try a colour-changing cocktail at the Alchemist
address_text: The Alchemist, 63-66 St Martins Lane, London WC2N 4JS
description_html: The Alchemist is a hip and cosy bar with top-notch cocktails. Expect colour-changing, taste-changing, smoke-emitting, fire-blazing cocktails, that are sure to impress.

name: Kanada-Ya - Covent Garden
headline: Try truffle ramen or a flavourful tonkotsu at Kanada-Ya
address_text: Kanada-Ya, Covent Garden, 64 St Giles High Street, London WC2H 8LE
description_html: There are a number of ramen options in London, but few can deliver bowls of noodles that are as outstanding as Kanada-Ya. Try their Tonkotsu with soft chashu pork belly and crunchy wood ear mushroom. For something for unique, their Truffle ramen is to die for - pork bone broth with infusions of truffle paste and white truffle oil.

name: Monohon
headline: Try delicious (Londoner-crafted) ramen and soba at Monohon
description_html: Founded by an ex-corporate Londoner who decided to move to Japan to learn how to make ramen, Monohon delivers some of the best bowls of noodles in London. This cosy outpost offers ramen and soba at reasonable prices and of top quality.

name: Menya Ramen
headline: Have an authentic bowl of ramen at Menya
address_text: Menya Ramen, 29 Museum St, Holborn, London WC1A 1LH
description_html: Hidden away on a side-street, Menya is a casual spot to grab a bowl of delicious and authentic Japanese ramen. Their menu is short and to the point. Ideal spot for a first date or a stop on the way to another destination.

name: Padella
headline: Order delicious pasta dishes at Padella
description_html: The acclaim Padella has received is well-deserved - this cosy spot offers incredible pastas to share at very reasonable prices. We recommend at least three pasta dishes per couple. While their menu is ever-rotating, the "Pappardelle with 8 hours Dexter beef shin ragu" and the "Pici cacio & pepe" are ever popular. There will likely be a wait, so write your name down on arrival and go for a drink around the many bars surrounding nearby Borough Market while you wait for your table.

name: Duck & Waffle - Restaurant
headline: Enjoy a waffle in a stylish venue overlooking 360 views of London, at Duck & Waffle
description_html: Duck & Waffle, with its modern decor and 360 London skyscraper views, is probably most famous for serving waffles 24 hours a day. During themore reasonable hours you can book a table and try their signature duck leg and waffle dish, and try their unique and delicious small plates. The setting is perfect for a stylish and romantic meal. Pro tip: the glass elevator to the 38th floor will give you a rush as you look out over the city.

name: Duck & Waffle - Bar
headline: Have a cocktail and enjoy London skyline views at the stylish Duck & Waffle
description_html: The bar at Duck & Waffle is stylish, modern and romantic, boasting beautiful London skyscraper views. It is a common spot for out of towners given the atmosphere and trendy vibes.  Pro tip: the glass elevator to the 38th floor will give you a rush as you look out over the city.

name: SushiSamba - Bar - The City
headline: Enjoy skyline views, hip beats and cocktails at the trendy SushiSamba
description_html: SushiSamba's sexy rooptop bar has beats, cocktails and a beautiful scenery. Step into their indoor bar for a Japanese themed area with sweeping skyline views of London. This is a perfectly fun and intimate location to end the night.

name: Madison - Bar
headline: Enjoy skyline views over St.Paul's and a beautiful outdoor terrace at Madison
address_text: Madison Restaurant, Rooftop Terrace, One New Change, St Paul’s, London EC4M 9AF
description_html: Madison has some of the best rooftop bar views in London, with a beautiful viewing area over St.Paul's. In the winter, heat lamps keep the outdoor area warm. Go on a Friday or Saturday night for great beats and more of a party atmosphere.

name: Hoppers Soho
headline: Try mouthwatering Sri Lankan food at Hoppers Soho
description_html: Hoppers is a super popular London hotspot for Sri Lankan food. At prime times, get there early to put your name on the waitlist - you can go grab a drink at a bar nearby as you can count on the fact that there will be a wait. Their signature "hoppers" (large crispy pancakes) are a must try, as well as their bone marrow curry and devilled prawns.

name: Din Tai Fung
headline: Enjoy dim sum and top-notch Shanghainese soup dumplings at Din Tai Fung
address_text: Din Tai Fung, 5-6 Henrietta Street, Covent Garden, London WC2E 8PS
description_html: Straight out of Taiwan, Din Tai Fung has become a global sensation. They are most famous for their xiao long bao, delicious pork dumplings filled with soup. Get ready to share new foods as their menu is dim sum style. The restaurant doesn't accept reservations but you can grab a drink (or a Taiwanese bubble tea) at their bar while you wait for a table.

name: Barrica
headline: Feast on delicious Spanish tapas plates at Barrica
description_html: Barrica's tapas are authentic, delicious and not to be missed. Try the Galician octopus, bellota jamón (sliced ham pigs fed soley acorns), patatas bravas, and the cuttle fish black ink rice. The atmosphere is cosy and intimate and the neighbourhood is bustling.

name: Saltyard
headline: Taste Spanish-Italian fusion tapas at Saltyard
description_html: Saltyard is a fusion of Spanish and Italian cuisine, specialising in small plates and charcuterie. Here you can enjoy variations on familiar Spanish tapas favourites, while enjoying the cosy and intimate atmosphere.

name: Skypod at Skygarden
headline: Enjoy 360 London views and a beautiful indoor rooftop garden at Skypod
address_text: Sky Garden, 1 Sky Garden Walk, London EC3M 8AF
description_html: Skypod is the bar at London's Skygarden, a (covered) rooftop garden with a 360 degree view of London. Walk-ins are welcome without a booking in the evenings, which are the best time to go to see the skyscrapers and bridges of London lit up. Cocktails are tasty, and the views along the walking path perimeter of the rooftop will keep the conversation flowing as fast as the drinks.
